      <h2 class="section-title section-title-glow">Job search coaching vs. career coaching — what's the difference?</h2>
      <p>Job search coaching is a subset of career coaching focused specifically on the execution phase — when you know what you want and need help executing the search effectively. Career coaching is broader: it may start with role clarity and positioning work before moving into job search execution.</p>
      <p>At Askia, most clients do both: we start with strategy and positioning, then move into active job search support. But if you already know exactly what role you are targeting and just need a better execution system, job search coaching is the right starting point.</p>
    </div>
