      <details class="faq-card" open>
        <summary>How long should a job search take with coaching?</summary>
        <p>With job search coaching, most professionals see their first interview within 21 days and land an offer within 60 days when executing the strategy consistently. Without a clear strategy, job searches routinely stretch to 4–9 months — with significant cost in both lost compensation and mental health.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-card">
        <summary>I've been applying for months with no results. Can job search coaching fix that?</summary>
        <p>Usually yes — if you have been applying for months with no traction, the problem is almost always positioning rather than lack of effort. Job search coaching starts with diagnosing exactly where the breakdown is: resume quality, LinkedIn signal, targeting precision, or application volume. Once the root cause is clear, the fix is usually faster than most people expect.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-card">
        <summary>Is job search coaching the same as having a recruiter?</summary>
        <p>No. A recruiter works for the employer and submits you for roles they are hired to fill. Job search coaching works exclusively in your interest — building your positioning, strategy, and execution system so you are competitive for any role you pursue, not just the ones a recruiter happens to have open. See our full <a href="/career-coach-vs-recruiter/">career coach vs. recruiter breakdown</a>.</p>
      </details>
